Alembic migrations for the Personal Monitor backend.

The database URL is read from the DATABASE_URL environment variable at runtime
(see env.py); it falls back to local SQLite when unset.

Common commands (run from personal-monitor-backend/):

  alembic upgrade head                      # apply all migrations
  alembic revision --autogenerate -m "msg"  # create a migration from model changes
  alembic downgrade -1                       # roll back one migration
  alembic current                            # show current DB revision
  alembic history                            # list migrations

On Render the start command runs `alembic upgrade head` automatically before
launching the server, so deploys keep the schema up to date.
